  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Classic Twin Rooms</strong> sleep two people and are around 20m² with north facing views</p>
<p><strong>Classic Triple Rooms</strong> sleep three people and are around 20m² with an additional single bed and north facing views</p>
<p><strong>Classic South-Facing Twin Rooms</strong> sleep two to three people and are around 20m² with an additional sofa bed (suitable for a child up to 10 yrs) and south facing views</p>
<p><strong>Classic Panoramic View Rooms</strong> sleep two to three people and are around 20m² with an additional sofa bed (suitable for a child up to 10 yrs) and south facing panoramic views</p>
<p>Twin rooms for single use are available with a supplement. Adjacent rooms can be requested if they are the same type.</p>
<p><strong>Room facilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Twin or double beds (please specify preference when booking)</li>
<li>Mountain views</li>
<li>Wi-Fi (additional charge payable locally)</li>
<li>Satellite TV</li>
<li>Safe</li>
<li>Telephone</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
<li>Mini-bar</li>
<li>Bath and WC</li>
<li>Twin rooms will fit a baby cot with two adults sharing. </li>
</ul>]]></roomsDescription>
